    "This framework, known as Xception, considerably surpasses Inception V3 on a bigger image classification sample that consists of 350 million images and 17,000 classes, outperforming Inception V3 on the ImageNet dataset (about which Inception V3 was built).",
    "The model is substantially lightweight and has fewer components, which is its major benefit.",
    "ResNeXtResNeXt is designed for efficient image classification.",
    "The architecture of ResNeXt consist of stacks of topology blocks.",
